'''柏德列·理察·"柏迪"·麥卡菲'''（{{lang-en|'''Patrick Richard "Paddy" McCarthy'''}}，{{bd|1983年|5月31日|catidx=McCarthy, Patrick}}）在[[爱尔兰共和国|爱尔兰共和国]][[首都|首都]][[都柏林|都柏林]]出生，是一名職業足球員，司職[[後衛_(足球)|後衛]]。

==生平==
<!--McCarthy joined [[Leicester_City_F.C.|Leicester City]] in March 2005 for a fee of £100,000 from [[Manchester_City_F.C.|Manchester City]], signing a three-year contract.<ref name="Foxes land City stopper">{{cite news| title = Foxes land City stopper| url = http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11679_2328528,00.html| publisher = Sky Sports| date = 2005-03-03| accessdate = 2009-04-15}}</ref> He had never played for Manchester City's first team but had enjoyed loan spells at [[Boston_United_F.C.|Boston United]] and [[Notts_County_F.C.|Notts County]] during 2002 and 2003. Boston had made a bid to sign McCarthy on a permanent basis in February 2003.<ref name="Boston bid for McCarthy">{{cite news| title = Boston bid for McCarthy| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/boston_united/2795453.stm| publisher = BBC Sport| date = 2003-02-24| accessdate = 2007-08-24}}</ref>

McCarthy became a favourite with the Leicester fans, due to his no-nonsense style of play, and in July 2006 was named club captain for the [[2006-07_in_English_football|2006–07]] season. His season was cut short when he dislocated his shoulder in a training accident in February 2007.<ref name="McCarthy shoulder blow for Foxes">{{cite news|title = McCarthy shoulder blow for Foxes|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/l/leicester_city/6355467.stm|publisher = BBC Sport|date = 2007-02-15|accessdate = 2010-02-12}}</ref> Nonetheless, McCarthy expressed his wish to leave Leicester before the start of next season, despite being offered a new contract.<ref name="Allen regrets McCarthy departure">{{cite news|title = Allen regrets McCarthy departure|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/l/leicester_city/6731369.stm|publisher = BBC Sport|date = 2007-06-07|accessdate = 2010-02-12}}</ref>

